The popular tour broking firm, Ufitfly has unveiled its plan for soccer lovers that might want to take a tour of Qatar for the FIFA Club World Cup slated for Doha. Interested soccer lovers, according to Ajibola Ogunkeyede would have opportunity to watch the 16th edition of the tournament between winners of the six continental confederations, which holds from e December 11 -22. The eight football matches to be played involves six teams at three different stadiums. One of the highpoint of the tournament is watching Liverpool FC play on Wednesday 18th December at the semi-final with special provision for Nigerian Liverpool fans that might want to witness the epic game. “At Ufitfly, we will depart Nigeria, December 16th till 22nd as we go on a tour of these wonderful cities where these matches will be played”, the statement reads.